<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-55f8ebc805e65b5b71ddafdae390e3be2bcd69af">Description</h2>
ToME:Recentered is exactly the same as standard ToME 2.3.x, except that the initial skill and ability levels have been adjusted in an attempt to approximate the starting ability levels of ToME 2.2.7; in exchange for this power boost, skill point gain is restored to 5 per level.  If you've been playing standard ToME 2.3.x and found it extremely difficult to find secret doors, disarm traps or hit monsters with low-level characters, you might want to give this module a try. <h2 id="head-a69ab6442fa5e4ed9de9974074737205958697f1">Module Version</h2>
0.0.2a:  "Let's Try This Again...", maintenance release <p>
Changes since 0.0.2: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Incorporated data file changes from 2.3.2. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
Changes since 0.0.1: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Oops, Z/Cth monsters aren't blocked in modules; remove them from <tt>edit/r_info.txt</tt>. <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/redface.png" alt=":o" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


